},"children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"gc-lbl","children":"— Root cause addressed this month"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"gc-val","children":"Auth workflow updated — same denial won't repeat."}]]}]]}]}]]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"block","id":"pain","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"container","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"block-head fade-in","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"eyebrow","children":"The denial cycle that never ends"}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"display","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"You are not fixing denials. <em>You are clearing them.</em>"}}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"monologue fade-in","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"","children":"A denial comes in. Someone on the billing team reviews it, makes a correction, and resubmits. The claim pays. The team moves on."}],["$","p","1",{"className":"","children":"Next month, the exact same denial shows up. Same reason code. Same payer. Different patient, different date — same problem. Because the correction was a patch, not a fix. The claim was cleared from the queue, but the workflow gap that caused it was never addressed."}],["$","p","2",{"className":"highlight","children":"\"Your team is not doing denial management. They are doing denial recovery — putting out the same fire, in the same room, every single month. Until someone traces why the fire keeps starting.\""}],["$","p","3",{"className":"","children":"That is denial fixation. Not just working the denial — finding the upstream cause, correcting the claim, building the right appeal, and closing the workflow gap so the same problem does not repeat. It is the difference between managing your denial rate and actually reducing it."}]]}]]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"block block--warm","id":"pain-details","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"container","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"block-head fade-in","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"eyebrow","children":"Why denials keep repeating"}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"display","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Denials are symptoms. The root cause is always <em>somewhere upstream.</em>"}}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-ledger fade-in","children":[["$","div","01",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"01"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Eligibility was wrong before the visit"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"A patient's insurance changed. The front desk did not catch it. The claim went out against inactive or incorrect coverage. Working the denial does not prevent the next one. Fixing the eligibility verification process does."}]]}]]}],["$","div","02",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"02"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Authorization was missing or expired at time of service"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The visit happened. The claim was submitted. The payer denied it for no valid authorization. This is a pre-service workflow gap — and fixing the denial after the fact does not close that gap for next month."}]]}]]}],["$","div","03",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"03"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Coding contained a preventable error"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"A missing modifier, an incorrect diagnosis link, a procedure requiring documentation that was not attached. These errors are not random — they are usually the result of a recurring knowledge gap or a workflow step being skipped under pressure."}]]}]]}],["$","div","04",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"04"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Payer-specific billing rules were not followed"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Every payer has its own requirements. When those rules are not reflected in the team's daily practice, claims keep failing for the same reason until someone tracks the pattern and corrects it at the source — not claim by claim."}]]}]]}],["$","div","05",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"05"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Documentation did not support the billed procedure"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The provider documented the visit. The coder billed based on what was written. The payer denied it because the documentation did not meet their specific criteria for that code level. This is a clinical-billing communication gap that repeats until someone brings both sides together."}]]}]]}],["$","div","06",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"06"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Appeals are filed without strong supporting documentation"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"An appeal is submitted with a one-line explanation and no clinical notes or payer-specific reasoning. The payer upholds the denial. The practice accepts the outcome. But a properly constructed appeal would have reversed it."}]]}]]}],["$","div","07",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"07"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Denial trends are never analyzed across the payer mix"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Each denial is treated as an individual event. Nobody pulls back to ask whether a specific payer is denying a specific procedure at a higher-than-expected rate — which would indicate either a payer error, a contract issue, or a systemic billing problem."}]]}]]}]]}]]}]}],"$undefined",["$","section",null,{"className":"block block--ink","id":"solution","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"container","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"block-head fade-in","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"eyebrow","children":"Denial fixation — what we do"}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"display display--light","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"We do not just work the denial. <em>We find out why it happened and make sure it stops.</em>"}}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Most denial management services work claims. We do too — but we also document the pattern, trace the root cause, and address the upstream workflow gap. That is what we mean by fixation: the problem is identified and fixed, not just cleared from the queue."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"two-col fade-in","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"process-list","children":[["$","div","01",{"className":"process-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"process-num","children":"01"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Denial received and categorized within 24–48 hours"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Every denial reviewed, assigned a root cause category, and entered into the tracking system. No denial sits in a queue without a category and an owner assigned to it."}]]}]]}],["$","div","02",{"className":"process-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"process-num","children":"02"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Root cause traced to the upstream origin"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"We trace every denial back to where the problem started — eligibility, authorization, charge entry, coding, documentation, or submission error. The claim is not corrected until the actual cause is identified."}]]}]]}],["$","div","03",{"className":"process-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"process-num","children":"03"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Claim corrected at the source of the error"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The correction addresses the actual cause, not just the denial code. If the denial reason is \"authorization required,\" the correction includes documenting why authorization was or was not obtained — not just adding a modifier."}]]}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"classNam